metadata.name: Fuel Oil No. 1 (Jet A-1)
alternate_names: Turbo Fuel A-1, Jet A-1 Kerosene; Carburant A de turbo-moteur, Jet A-1 Kérosène

reference.reference: Harris, G., The Comparative Toxicity of Crude and Refined Oils to Daphnia Magna, Environment Canada Manuscript Report Number EE-152, Ottawa, Ontario, 29 pp., 1992

metadata.comments: A petroleum distillate blended from Kerosene fractions and used in civil aviation. Jet A-1 is similar to Jet A except for a lower freezing point. Operational fuel for all turboprop and turbojet aircraft requiring a low freezing point product.
